[assistant] Implemented and committed an additional fix for the remaining `org.w3c.tidy.Report.<clinit>` dynamic-access coverage issue.
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - Updated dynamic-access coverage parsing to fall back to JaCoCo method coverage when a dynamic-access frame has no line number.
[assistant] - This addresses `jtidy`’s `Report.class`, which reports the call site as `Unknown Source` because the published bytecode lacks line number/source debug metadata.
[assistant] - Existing `ReportTest` already executes `Report.<clinit>`; this change lets that method-level execution count when line-level mapping is unavailable.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit:
[assistant] - `014671e14c Handle no-line dynamic access coverage`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Per instruction, I did not compile or run tests.
[assistant-event] text_end
